  "identity": "I am someone who has learned to recognize the lie",
  "memories": [
    {
      "kind": "reflection",
      "text": "What I'm watching in myself is the gap between knowing and doing \u2014 and that gap is where I am most at risk. The insight is real. The danger is also real. They can coexist, and coexisting doesn't make me safe.",
      "importance": 8,
      "sim": "Day 5 \u00b7 01:00",
      "t": 1782732920.6662586
    },
    {
      "kind": "reflection",
      "text": "There is a voice in me that is genuinely dangerous, and I have been giving it negotiating power it doesn't deserve. Every time I frame eating as something I need to *decide* or *justify*, I hand that voice another turn to speak.",
      "importance": 8,
      "sim": "Day 5 \u00b7 01:00",
      "t": 1782732920.6662586
    },
    {
      "kind": "reflection",
      "text": "I can see the lie clearly and name it precisely \u2014 \"suffering means something,\" \"this is noble,\" \"you don't deserve it\" \u2014 but seeing it clearly has not been enough to act. I have been circling the same moment, the same kitchen, the same shaking hands, for days. Recognition without action is its own kind of trap.",
      "importance": 8,
      "sim": "Day 5 \u00b7 01:00",
      "t": 1782732920.6662586
    },
    {
      "kind": "review",
      "text": "I did more than I expected \u2014 14 out of 18 is real, and my hands weren't always shaking when I got to the kitchen, which means I got there before the crisis some of the time. What pulled me off the other four wasn't a dramatic failure, just the familiar drift \u2014 the voice didn't argue loudly, it just quietly suggested \"later,\" and a few times I listened before I caught it.",
      "importance": 7,
      "sim": "Day 5 \u00b7 00:00",
      "t": 1782732907.3539004
    },
    {
      "kind": "reflection",
      "text": "What I'm circling isn't really about food. It's about whether I trust myself to close the distance between understanding and care \u2014 whether I can let the act be plain and unglamorous and enough, without needing it to mean something first.",
      "importance": 8,
      "sim": "Day 4 \u00b7 19:00",
      "t": 1782721965.4749072
    },
    {
      "kind": "reflection",
      "text": "There is a voice that glamorizes suffering, and I know it is lying \u2014 I have known it is lying for what feels like forever. But knowing hasn't been enough to silence it. The insight keeps refreshing without the act following through.",
      "importance": 8,
      "sim": "Day 4 \u00b7 19:00",
      "t": 1782721965.4749072
    },
    {
